font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">2 People</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top; width:137px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">3-7 People</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top; width:137px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">$169</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top; width:137px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">$97.50</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top; width:137px\">\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">$82.50</span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 1, NULL, 2, 1, '2020-04-29 11:19:56', 1, 1, '2020-04-27 09:53:31');
INSERT INTO `tour_item` VALUES (54, 1, 1, 'Sunrise Over Angkor Wat and The Classic Grand Circuit', '/backend/web/uploads/siem_reap_angkor_adventures/tour-item/sunrise angkor_20200427100709.jpg', 'Sunrise over the towers of Angkor Wat has to be one of the most magnificent sights in the world, and what better way to begin your tour of the gems of the Khmer Empire.', 55.00, 8, '05:00:00', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">(Preah Khan, Neak Pean, Ta Som, East Mebon, Pre Rup)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Sunrise over the towers of Angkor Wat has to be one of the most magnificent sights in the world, and what better way to begin your tour of the gems of the Khmer Empire.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">After this amazing start we go to Preah Khan, the Khmer Empire&rsquo;s University and a wonderful place to see native birds today.&nbsp; This large temple complex supported almost 6000 villages and 100 thousand people at its height in the 12th century and contains the only remaining mundane two-story building of the Empire.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Despite the small size of our next temple, Neak Pean, it is one the most important sites in Angkor.&nbsp; The island temple is in a complex of 5 pools, which also hold symbolic statues emerging from the waters.&nbsp; The central pool held healing waters and was a popular pilgrimage site.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Next we visit either Ta Som or the East Mebon and Pre Rup, depending upon what takes your fancy.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Ta Som is a smaller 12th century temple built by Jayavarman VII, it has been left largely unrestored other than site stabilization since it was rediscovered swallowed by the jungle in the 1930s.&nbsp; One of the most photogenic sites in Angkor is the Sacred Fig growing over the gopura (entrance gate) at Ta Som.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">East Mebon and Pre Rup were built by the same 10th century King in the same style and are in North/South alignment over the baray. East Mebon was once an island temple; from the top you can imagine the view over the waters of the Baray to the former city. Pre Rup is a pyramid temple representing Mount Meru and dedicated to Shiva.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>INCLUSIONS</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Private car with English speaking driver</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Air Conditioned car ensures a comfortable day of exploring</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Flat-rate pricing for up to eight passengers is ideal for groups</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles from and to your Siem Reap hotel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Mineral water and cold towel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">24 hours support by our team</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>What to Expect</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Get up early to be picked up at your hotel and taken to purchase the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket, if you don&rsquo;t already have it.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">The route is tailored to you and starts with sunrise at Angkor Wat then Preah Khan, then continues to Neak Pean. From there we can seek out the photogenic tree at Ta Som, or visit the East Mebon and Pre Rup.&nbsp; You will be returned to your drop off point after a flexible day of exploring.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Exclusions:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Angkor Archaeological Park ticket</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Meals and Beverages</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Know Before You Book</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Round-trip transportation is available from most centrally located Siem Reap hotels. Please arrange pickup from your hotel or a nearby location when you call to confirm your reservation.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Please be ready and waiting in your hotel lobby 15 minutes prior to your scheduled pick-up time.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not wheelchair accessible.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not suitable for children under 6 years old</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">USD 37 for the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket can be purchased on the day if required.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Car with driver (4 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 3 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 55 per day (max 8 hours)</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Van with driver (8-12 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 8 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 70 per day(max 8 hours)</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 1, NULL, 2, 1, '2020-04-27 12:11:02', 1, 1, '2020-04-27 10:07:09');
INSERT INTO `tour_item` VALUES (55, 1, 1, 'Sunrise Over Angkor Wat and the Treasures of the Khmer Empire', '/backend/web/uploads/siem_reap_angkor_adventures/tour-item/SunriseAngkor_20200427101055.jpg', 'Sunrise at Angkor Wat is one of the most magnificent sights in the world, and it is an awesome beginning to an amazing tour.', 55.00, 8, '05:00:00', '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">(Angkor Wat, Angkor Thom, Bayon, Terrace of the Leper King, Terrace of the Elephants, Ta Prohm)</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Sunrise over Angkor Wat is a magnificent sight and what better way to start your day off exploring the treasures of the Khmer Empire?&nbsp; Angkor Wat, Angkor Thom, the Bayon, the Terrace of the Elephant and the Terrace of the Leper King plus Ta Prohm are all included in this tour with expert and interesting commentary from your guide.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">You will be picked up early from your hotel and taken to buy the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket, if required, before going to Angkor Wat to witness the spectacular sunrise over its towers.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">After exploring the largest religious monument in the world, we go to the former Imperial Khmer Capital city of Angkor Thom, once the largest city in the world.&nbsp; While in this ancient city we visit the former State Temple of the Bayon.&nbsp; This unique temple has over 200 smiling faces gazing benevolently out over the former city, and bas relief depicting life here in the 12th&nbsp;century.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Our next stop is at the former Imperial ceremonial monuments of the Terrace of the Elephants and the Terrace of the Leper King. From here the Kings of Angkor held celebrations and victory parades. It was the Khmer Empire&rsquo;s National Mall, Buckingham Palace and Champs-Elysees all rolled into one.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Then we venture to the Khmer Empire&rsquo;s huge monastery temple, Ta Prohm.&nbsp; This jungle covered temple was featured in the movie &ldquo;Tomb Raider&rdquo; and also has a very controversial carving.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Because this is a small group tour, you will have the opportunity to ask your very knowledgeable local guide any questions you may have about the temples and the Khmer Empire.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Of course, you are returned to your hotel at the end of the tour.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">INCLUSIONS</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Private car with English speaking driver</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Air Conditioned car ensures a comfortable day of exploring</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Flat-rate pricing for up to eight passengers, ideal for groups</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles from and to your Siem Reap hotel</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Mineral water and cold towel</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">24 hours support by our team</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">&nbsp;Exclusions:</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Angkor Archaeological Park ticket</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Meals and Beverages</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">What to Expect</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">After an early departure from your hotel, we take you to buy your Angkor Archaeological Park ticket, if required then proceed to Angkor Wat for sunrise and exploring the temple.&nbsp; Afterwards we go to Angkor Thom, the Bayon, the Terrace of the Elephant and the Terrace of the Leper King and finally Ta Prohm before returning you to your hotel.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Know Before You Book</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Round-trip transportation is available from most centrally located Siem Reap hotels. Please arrange pickup from your hotel or a nearby location when you call to confirm your reservation.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Please be ready and waiting in your hotel lobby 15 minutes prior to your scheduled pick-up time.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">This activity is not wheelchair accessible.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">This activity is not suitable for children under 6 years old</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">USD 37 for the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket can be purchased on the day if required.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"Table\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Car with driver (4 seats)</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Maximum 3 pax</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">US$ 55 per day (8 hours max)</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Van with driver (8-12 seats)</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Maximum 8 pax</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">US$ 66 per day (8 hours max)</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 1, NULL, 2, 1, '2020-04-27 12:01:58', 1, 1, '2020-04-27 10:10:55');
INSERT INTO `tour_item` VALUES (56, 1, 1, 'The Classic Grand Circuit', '/backend/web/uploads/siem_reap_angkor_adventures/tour-item/Preah Khan_20200427101459.jpg', 'This classic tour of the Grand Circuit begins at the less frequented but magnificent Preah Khan, the Khmer Empireâ€™s University and a wonderful place to see native birds today.Â  ', 45.00, 8, '09:00:00', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">(Preah Khan, Neak Pean, Ta Som, East Mebon, Pre Rup)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This classic tour of the Grand Circuit begins at the less frequented but magnificent Preah Khan, the Khmer Empire&rsquo;s University and a wonderful place to see native birds today.&nbsp; This large temple complex supported almost 6000 villages and 100 thousand people at its height in the 12th century and contains the only remaining mundane two-story building of the Empire.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Despite the small size of our next temple, Neak Pean, it is one the most important sites in Angkor.&nbsp; The island temple is in a complex of 5 pools, which also hold symbolic statues emerging from the waters.&nbsp; The central pool held healing waters and was a popular pilgrimage site.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Next we visit either Ta Som or the East Mebon and Pre Rup, depending upon what takes your fancy.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Ta Som is a smaller 12th century temple built by Jayavarman VII, it has been left largely unrestored other than site stabilization since it was rediscovered swallowed by the jungle in the 1930s.&nbsp; One of the most photogenic sites in Angkor is the Sacred Fig growing over the gopura (entrance gate) at Ta Som.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">East Mebon and Pre Rup were built by the same 10th century King in the same style and are in North/South alignment over the baray. East Mebon was once an island temple, from the top you can imagine the view over the waters of the Baray to the former city. Pre Rup is a pyramid temple representing Mount Meru and dedicated to Shiva.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>INCLUSIONS</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Private car with English speaking driver</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Air Conditioned car ensures a comfortable day of exploring</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Flat-rate pricing for up to eight passengers is ideal for groups</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles from and to your Siem Reap hotel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Mineral water and cold towel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">24 hours support by our team</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>What to Expect</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Your driver will pick you up at your hotel and take you to purchase the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket, if you don&rsquo;t already have it.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">The route is tailored to you but starts at Preah Khan, then continues to Neak Pean. From there we can seek out the photogenic tree at Ta Som, or visit the East Mebon and Pre Rup.&nbsp; You will be returned to your drop off point after a flexible day of exploring.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Exclusions:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Angkor Archaeological Park ticket</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Meals and Beverages</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Know Before You Book</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Round-trip transportation is available from most centrally located Siem Reap hotels. Please arrange pickup from your hotel or a nearby location when you call to confirm your reservation.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Please be ready and waiting in your hotel lobby 15 minutes prior to your scheduled pick-up time.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not wheelchair accessible.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not suitable for children under 6 years old</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">USD 37 for the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket can be purchased on the day if required.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Car with driver (4 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 3 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 45 per day</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Van with driver (8-12 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 8</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 60 per day</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 1, NULL, 2, 1, '2020-04-27 11:57:06', 1, 1, '2020-04-27 10:14:59');
INSERT INTO `tour_item` VALUES (57, 1, 1, 'The Awesome Temples of the Khmer Empire', '/backend/web/uploads/siem_reap_angkor_adventures/tour-item/fe_20200427102110.jpg', 'This is the classic tour of the â€œBig Threeâ€ temples of the Khmer Empire. These are the most popular and considered to be the temples visitors must see while they are here, Angkor Wat, Ta Prohm and the Bayon in Angkor Thom.', 45.00, 8, '09:00:00', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">(Angkor Wat, Angkor Thom, Bayon, Ta Prohm)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This is the classic tour of the &ldquo;Big Three&rdquo; temples of the Khmer Empire. These are the most popular and considered to be the temples visitors must see while they are here, Angkor Wat, Ta Prohm and the Bayon in Angkor Thom. Your knowledgeable English speaking local guide will provide expert commentary and interesting on the history of the Khmer Empire and each temple, as well as they symbolism of the buildings and their decorations.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">After being picked up at your hotel, we head to Angkor Wat where your guide will accompany you around the largest religious monument in the world explaining this magnificent temple and its intricate bas reliefs and carvings.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Then we move onto the former Imperial Capital city of Angkor Thom, the largest city in the world at its height in the 12th&nbsp;century.&nbsp; Here we visit the former State Temple of the Bayon. This unique temple with its 218 smiling faces gazing benevolently over the former city has amazing bas relief round the interior walls depicting life in the city over 800 years ago.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">After lunch we go to the former monastery temple, Ta Prohm.&nbsp; This jungle covered temple once supported almost 100 thousand people, and more recently was used in the filming of the movie &ldquo;Tomb Raider&rdquo;. It also has a controversial carving of what looks a little like a dinosaur but is most likely to be an extinct rhinoceros with the jungle, or flames depicted behind it.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Absorb a late evening breeze and enjoy the peaceful, rural atmosphere before heading back to your hotel.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>INCLUSIONS</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Private car with English speaking driver</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Air conditioned car ensures a comfortable day of exploring</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Flat-rate pricing for up to eight passengers, ideal for groups</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles from and to your Siem Reap hotel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Mineral water and cold towel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">24 hours support by our team</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>What to Expect</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">After pickup at your hotel, board a climate-controlled vehicle for the trip to the Angkor Archaeological Park and Angkor Wat.&nbsp;The next stop is the Bayon Temple in the ancient city of Angkor Thom, then Ta Prohm.&nbsp; You are returned to your hotel at the end of the tour.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Exclusions:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Angkor Archaeological Park ticket</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Meals and Beverages</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Know Before You Book</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Round-trip transportation is available from most centrally located Siem Reap hotels. Please arrange pickup from your hotel or a nearby location when you call to confirm your reservation.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Please be ready and waiting in your hotel lobby 15 minutes prior to your scheduled pick-up time.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not wheelchair accessible.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not suitable for children under 6 years old</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">USD 37 for the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket can be purchased on the day if required.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Car with driver (4 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 3 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 45 per day</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Van with driver (8-12 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 8</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 50 per day</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 1, NULL, 2, 1, '2020-04-27 11:20:50', 1, 1, '2020-04-27 10:21:10');
INSERT INTO `tour_item` VALUES (58, 1, 1, 'The Gems Of The Khmer Empire', '/backend/web/uploads/siem_reap_angkor_adventures/tour-item/Banteay Srei (24)_20200427102842.jpg', 'We begin at Angkor Wat, one of South-East Asiaâ€™s most important ancient sites. Then we go into the ancient city of Angkor Thom, the largest city in the world at its height and visit the Bayon Temple, followed by Ta Prohm and Banteay Srei.', 60.00, 8, '09:00:00', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">(Angkor Wat, Angkor Thom, Bayon, Ta Prohm, Banteay Srei)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This tour will cover the essential must-see sights and most famous temples of the Khmer Empire in air-conditioned comfort. The largest Religious monument in the world, Angkor Wat, the Temple of Tomb-Raider fame, Ta Prohm, the Bayon with its hundreds of enigmatic smiling faces in Angkor Thom and the &ldquo;Jewel of Khmer Art&rdquo;, Banteay Srei are all included in this tour.&nbsp; It is the perfect tour for those with limited time.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">We begin at Angkor Wat, one of South-East Asia&rsquo;s most important ancient sites. Then we go into the ancient city of Angkor Thom, the largest city in the world at its height and visit the Bayon Temple. This temple covered with more than 200 gently smiling Buddha faces also has an enormous bas relief showing all aspects of life in the 12th Century Khmer Empire.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">After this we move onto King Jayavarman VII&rsquo;s University dedicated to his mother, Ta Prohm. This jungle covered temple is where the movie Tomb Raider was filmed and has one of the most controversial carvings in South East Asia.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Then we travel through the beautiful Cambodian countryside, passing interesting villages, fields and jungle to the &ldquo;Jewel of the Khmer Empire&rdquo;.&nbsp; Banteay Srei is renowned for its exquisite, intricate carvings in pink sandstone and is the most beautiful of all the Khmer Empire temples.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Our knowledgeable guide will provide interesting commentary throughout the day on the history of the Khmer Empire and explain the architecture and hidden symbolism of the temples and their carvings. As this is a small, private tour, you can ask any questions you may have.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">INCLUSIONS</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Private car with English speaking driver</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Air-Conditioned car ensures a comfortable day of exploring</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Flat-rate pricing for up to eight passengers is ideal for groups</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles from and to your Siem Reap hotel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Mineral water and cold towel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">24 hours support by our team</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>What to Expect</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">After pickup at your hotel, board a climate-controlled vehicle for the trip to the Angkor Archaeological Park and Angkor Wat. (Park ticket not included but can be purchased if required)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">The next stop is the Bayon Temple in the ancient city of Angkor Thom, then Ta Prohm.&nbsp; Afterwards we leave the Park for the drive through the countryside to Banteay Srei.&nbsp; You are returned to your hotel at the end of the tour.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Exclusions:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Angkor Archaeological Park ticket</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Meals and Beverages</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Know Before You Book</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Round-trip transportation is available from most centrally located Siem Reap hotels. Please arrange pickup from your hotel or a nearby location when you call to confirm your reservation.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Please be ready and waiting in your hotel lobby 15 minutes prior to your scheduled pick-up time.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not wheelchair accessible.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not suitable for children under 6 years old</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">USD 37 for the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket can be purchased on the day if required.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Car with driver (4 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 3 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 60 per day (max 8 hours)</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Van with driver (8-12 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 8 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 80 per day(max 8 hours)</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 1, NULL, 2, 1, '2020-04-27 11:52:03', 1, 1, '2020-04-27 10:28:42');
INSERT INTO `tour_item` VALUES (59, 1, 1, 'Explore 200 Years Of The Khmer Empire', '/backend/web/uploads/siem_reap_angkor_adventures/tour-item/IMG_1719_20200427103240.jpg', 'Explore more than 200 years of history and discover some ancient gems often missed by tourists. Our guide will provide you with expert commentary and as this is a small group tour, they can also answer all the questions you may have.', 60.00, 8, '11:00:00', '<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">(Banteay Srei, Preah Khan, Neak Pean, Pre Rup)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Explore more than 200 years of architectural history and discover some ancient gems often missed by tourists. Our guide will provide you with expert commentary and as this is a small group tour, they can also answer all the questions you may have. Our air-conditioned vehicles will keep you cool throughout the day.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">The first temple is Pre Rup, the 10th Century brick and laterite temple with its central staircase is one of the oldest in the Park.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Then we travel through the beautiful Cambodian countryside past interesting villages, through fields and jungle to the &ldquo;Jewel of Khmer Art&rdquo;.&nbsp; The 10th century Banteay Srei Temple with the most exquisite and intricate carvings in pink sandstone, is the only temple not constructed by Royalty. After exploring this stunning temple in its beautiful setting and having lunch we head 200 years into the future to two 12th century monuments built by King Jayavarman VII.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">The island temple of Neak Pean was built as a hospital, the waters of the pools surrounding it were believed to balance the body and cure illness.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Preah Khan was built as a university and is a wonderful jungle covered explorer&rsquo;s paradise and a haven for bird-watchers.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">At each site, your guide explains the historical context, the architecture, symbolism and hidden meanings.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Of course, hotel pickup and drop-off are included for your convenience.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>INCLUSIONS</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Private vehicle with English speaking driver</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Air conditioned vehicle ensures a comfortable day of exploring</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Flat-rate pricing for up to eight passengers is ideal for groups</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Transfers by private air-conditioned vehicles from and to your Siem Reap hotel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Mineral water and cold towel</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">24 hours support by our team</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>What to Expect</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">You will be picked up at your hotel by a climate-controlled vehicle for the trip to Pre Rup, a 10th-century Hindu temple with a grand central staircase. From there, continue to Banteay Srei, passing through the Cambodian countryside. Following some free time to enjoy lunch, we head to Neak Pean then to the atmospheric Preah Khan temple.&nbsp;Your tour concludes with drop-off at your hotel.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Exclusions:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Angkor Archaeological Park ticket</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Meals and Beverages</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\"><strong>Know Before You Book</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Round-trip transportation is available from most centrally located Siem Reap hotels. Please arrange pickup from your hotel or a nearby location when you call to confirm your reservation.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Please be ready and waiting in your hotel lobby 15 minutes prior to your scheduled pick-up time.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not wheelchair accessible.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">This activity is not suitable for children under 6 years old</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">USD 37 for the Angkor Archaeological Park ticket can be purchased on the day if required.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Car with driver (4 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 3 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 60 per day (max 8 hours)</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Van with driver (8-12 seats)</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">Maximum 8 pax</span></span></td>\r\n			<td scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif\">US$ 80 per day(max 8 hours)</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 1, NULL, 2, 1, '2020-04-29 11:41:11', 1, 1, '2020-04-27 10:32:40');
COMMIT;

-- ----------------------------
-- Table structure for tour_item_card
-- ----------------------------
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `tour_item_card`;
CREATE TABLE `tour_item_card` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `tour_item_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `session_id` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `company_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `name` varchar(250) DEFAULT NULL,
  `feature_image` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `description` mediumtext DEFAULT NULL,
  `cost` decimal(10,2) DEFAULT NULL,
  `amount` decimal(10,2) DEFAULT NULL,
  `duration` decimal(6,0) DEFAULT NULL,
  `starting_time` time DEFAULT NULL,
  `timestamp` time DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'expired_time',
  `tip_note` text DEFAULT NULL,
  `recommended` int(1) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT '0= not recommended, 1= recommended',
  `duration_type` int(11) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT '1= day, 2= hour',
  `updated_by` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `updated_date` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  `from_date` date DEFAULT NULL,
  `to_date` date DEFAULT NULL,
  `status` int(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `show_home_page` int(1) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT '1 = show, 0 = no show',
  `created_by` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_date` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  `adult` decimal(11,0) DEFAULT NULL,
  `child` decimal(11,0) DEFAULT NULL,
  `price_adult` decimal(10,2) DEFAULT NULL,
  `price_child` decimal(10,2) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`) USING BTREE
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=123 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

